Does it really matter?

LISA
Of course!  You saw that nobody could plant a bomb.  Unless it was planted before we came here.  Could it be self-destruction?  But for what reason?  Or was it an internal leak of something flammable?  Was there a major short circuit?

RICK
Who cares?  There was a robot, and it’s gone.  You get carried too far into details that no longer matter.

LISA turns at RICK and stares persuasively.

RICK (CONT’D)
Unless you have serious statements and suspicions in mind.  And you do have.

LISA
There is a worthy investigation to be done.  And it won’t be the last time we’re here.  I need to know where Grobyc came from and what his goals are.  And in 2038, things will just start to pick up.  I will pull Grobyc out from under the ground to study every tiny detail until I get to the meat of the truth.  And so it will be for the rest of my days.

TONI
You’re terrifying.

RICK, SHIRLEY and SAYLOR are nodding.

LISA
Yeah?  Thanks!

LISA continues walking.

2 minutes later.

SHIRLEY
Apple.

TONI
Electricity.

RICK
Yorkshire.

SAYLOR
Enigma.

LISA
Affirmative.

SHIRLEY
Affirmative is not a noun.

LISA
First word of your latest sentence doesn’t start with E.

Familiar voice is heard from the distance.

@???
*Saylor!*

SAYLOR
Guys, I think we need to quicken our step.

@???
*Saylor!  Wait for me!*

LISA
It’s pointless.  Wait.  The tone...  Toni, but you’re here.

TONI
Yes, I’m here.  Why do you ask?

@???
*Saylor!!*

LISA
Guys, you do notice that it’s the same voice, right?

SHIRLEY
But it can’t be her?

SAYLOR
This thought is unsettling.
(yelling in response, without turning around)
Toni, is that you?

@???
*Yes, it’s me!  Please, stay there!*

TONI
Saylor, if I-- if *she* harms you, I’ll take action.

SAYLOR turns around.

SAYLOR
Oh my God.  Toni??

TONI #2
Yes.  Gosh, you were a good distance away.

TONI pulls out a gun and points it at TONI #2.

TONI #2
Toni.

TONI
I died.

TONI #2
You didn’t.

TONI #2 is showing the gunshot wound.

SAYLOR
No blood?

TONI #2
I don’t have any in the first place.

SAYLOR recoils in shock.

LISA
Fascinating.  Are you really cut from the same cloth as I am?

TONI #2
YDUWNJKNCIWONAZPW.

TONI
I don’t talk like that.

LISA
Goodness me!  You’re from the same factory!  Well, I think we could change your hair, face, legs, clothes, and we could make a second Lisa!

RICK
One is enough, thanks.

LISA
Er, Toni, you can put your gun down.  She’s harmless.

TONI
Well, if you say so.

TONI holsters her gun.

RICK
(to TONI #2)
Seriously, are you an android?  How?

TONI #2
Lisa, you’ve sent me here.

RICK
(to LISA)
What?

LISA
I don’t remember that.

TONI #2
I know the future version of you.

LISA
My future self?  Sent you here?

TONI #2
Yes.  You didn’t have a physical body at that moment.  You instructed me to arrive here.

LISA
You mean, I could lose my body.

TONI #2
I’m not allowed to tell you that.

LISA
Something to do with the established points in time.

TONI #2
Yes.

LISA
When did I send you and what for?  To eliminate Grobyc with your hands?

TONI #2
That’s right.  I destroyed him with planted bombs that activated with a pistol shot.

LISA
Oh, I’m so good!

TONI #2
But the right time for sending me here will come naturally.  You’ll see.

LISA
Alright, I’ve got other things to worry about anyway.

TONI
But what happened to real me if it turns out that my death is faked?

TONI #2
Your adventures with Saylor continue.  You’re alive.

TONI
So, I don’t know when I die, just like Saylor.

RICK
It doesn’t matter.  Enjoy our company!

SAYLOR puts her arm around TONI.

SHIRLEY
If time travel has given you a longer life, just be grateful and accept this gift.

TONI
Well, I hope to savor every moment spent with you guys.  I don’t know what I’d do without you.

TONI #2
Guys, may I come with you?  I mean, I can’t stay here to play dead.

LISA
Guys, I suppose you could move closer together to make room for her.

SAYLOR
Er, heheh, I guess.  Shirley, do you mind?

SHIRLEY
Not a problem.

LISA
What a team!

Everyone continues on the path to the time machine.

RICK
Is it fair that there’s more comfort for us two?

LISA
I think--

RICK
--Ah, don’t tell me.  That’s your game.

LISA
No?  I think you could use your engineering gifts in our team effort to build a time bus.

RICK
Ha-ha, a time bus?

LISA
That’s your style of jokes.

RICK
Okay, you got me.  My turn, by the way.

LISA
Waited for this moment?

RICK
Oh hell yes.

LISA
And what if I throw you into the time vortex?  So I could be at the driver’s wheel all the time?

RICK
You can’t do that.  Who will be the person you test your games on?

LISA
I’ll find another human toy.

RICK
Oh will you really?  How many do you have in mind?

LISA
Hate the idea?  I’m glad.  It means that you’re stuck with me.

RICK
I’m free as a bird and I can do whatever I like.

LISA
I’m your cage and you don’t fully realize it yet.

RICK
Cage?  You?  Ha-ha!

LISA
Try to break me.

RICK
I’m not imprisoned.

LISA
I guess this could persuade you to see the invisible metal bars.

LISA removes her hand from her wrist to reveal a small digital indicator that starts counting down from 10 seconds.

RICK
Idiotic android!  You can’t casually start the self-destruction!

LISA
Just did.  Now, do you know how to stop it?

RICK
Stop the countdown!

LISA
Turn on the brains.

RICK
Okay.  I get it.  Reacts to the emotions.

LISA
I’m waiting.

RICK
I value you as a person and I don’t want to lose you.

Countdown stops at 2.  Numbers disappeared.  LISA puts her hand back on her wrist.

RICK (CONT’D)
But you manipulate me.

LISA
Wrong.  We’re both vulnerable.  And we must save each other.  Do you know why “must”?  Not because we require it from each other.  But because--

RICK
--You are valuable to me.

LISA
And you are valuable to me.  In the same way.  In fact, if you think about it, in human psychology, and in nature overall, this caring is leading to an affection.

RICK
So, do you have this feeling?

LISA
You didn’t think I was joking for nothing, right?

RICK
You can’t do unreasonable.

LISA
You can take a guess.  I think it’s pretty obvious.

RICK
So, roughly speaking, you see me as a romantic partner.

LISA
Gosh, that’s very straightforward.

RICK
Sorry.

LISA
Yes.

RICK
Mhm.

LISA
Yes, I do.  And the thing is: in a special way.  You know my character, I’m playful with everyone.  So... is it fine?

RICK
I don’t know.

LISA
Why?

RICK
Why me?

LISA
Can humans have specific preferences that are developing as they get along?

RICK
You’re not human.  But you’re trying your best at becoming one.

LISA
So your only problem is that I’m an android.

RICK
You’re a perfect human.

LISA
So?  What is the problem?

RICK
I don’t know.  I’m not ready for this.

LISA
Wait...  You’ve got used to the idea of being the lone wolf.  Solving personal problems alone.

RICK
Oh...  You see that, right?

LISA
You don’t have to live on your own.

RICK
Saylor said the same.

LISA
And she’s right.  We care about you.

RICK
I want to believe it.  I want to believe that these are not just the words said to comfort me.

LISA
Can you imagine what happens if we lose you?

RICK
Everyone will move on.  Like nothing happened.  Like a sweet moment that once was and gone.  You eat tasty food, and in an hour you forget how it tasted.  Like you didn’t eat it at all.

LISA
So that’s what first comes to your mind.  It really depends on how you make associations.

RICK
You want to tell me there is some “correct” way of thinking.

LISA
No.  You decide it for yourself.  But you know that for some people, the whole universe will be a darker place without you.  And that’s a loss they’ll never be able to make up for.  Yes, you see people moving on, because life continues.  But they can’t help but remember the best moments of their lives with your presence.

RICK
You don’t seem like the kind of person who would forget me.

LISA
Never in my life.

LISA and RICK laugh together and they put their arms around each other.

LISA
So what do you think about... well, quote: “seeing you as a romantic partner?”

RICK
I think something could work out for us.

LISA
Ooh, that’s the progress!  I knew that self-destruction trick would work on you.

RICK
What?  Was it fake?

LISA
I’m not a kamikaze.  I have that counter just for fun.

RICK
You’re a sly one.  Don’t remove it.  Can be helpful to fool others.

LISA
Ha-ha-ha, you read my mind!

SHIRLEY
Oh look at them.  Arguing, then making up.  The usual.

SAYLOR
Happens to the best of us.

CUT TO:

### Part 8

[[2 September 2024]]

EXT. 2038, HQ - Outside

