### Draft #2  •  End of Part 2

[[30 August 2024]]

LISA
I remember how you did rate Saylor.

SAYLOR
(gasps)
Did you?

RICK
As a joke.

SAYLOR
And?

RICK
Er...  8 out of 10.

Everyone gasped.

SAYLOR
Why not 9 or 10?

RICK
I have... other preferences.

SAYLOR
Huh.  Didn’t expect that from you.  Although, 8 out of 10.

RICK
What?

SAYLOR
You.  You’re 8 out of 10.  Same sentiment exactly.

SHIRLEY
It’s like you two share the same brain.

RICK
Yes.

SAYLOR ^
Yes.

RICK
I said first.

SAYLOR ^
I said first.

RICK
No, I did.

SAYLOR ^
No, I did.

RICK
Nevermind.

SAYLOR ^
Nevermind.

RICK
But I was first.

SAYLOR
Damn.

LISA
Also he rated Shirley.

SHIRLEY
Oh, did he really?

SAYLOR
Seems like he rated everyone.  Did you rate Eddie, by the way?

EDDIE
What?

LISA
Eddie: 7 out of 10.

EDDIE
Seriously?

RICK
As a joke.

EDDIE
Funny man.

RICK
Thanks.

EDDIE
And why not higher?

RICK
Really?

EDDIE
Or, okay, why not lower?  How did you rate at all?

RICK
Don’t ask me.  I don’t remember.  But that is an actual rating.  And I rated Shirley 9 out of 10.

SAYLOR
*What?!*

LISA
That’s correct.

SHIRLEY
Are you serious?

RICK
Okay, not as a joke this time.

SHIRLEY
And I didn’t know about it back then?

RICK
Sorry.

SHIRLEY
I’ll remember it then.  10 out of 10.

RICK
*Huh?!*

SAYLOR ^
*Huh?!*

SHIRLEY
I’ve already said why.  Sorry, Eddie, that’s retrospective anyway.

EDDIE
I understand.  That’s absolutely fair enough.  If I were you, I’d probably rate the same.

SAYLOR
Then it makes a difference.  *11 out of 10!*

LISA
This value is not allowed.

SAYLOR
*I don’t care.*  Rick deserves a better rating, and I’ll insist on it.
